  {"name":"Ken Ward","first_name":"Ken","last_name":"Ward","description":"Veteran climate activist from Corbett, Oregon and one of the five \"valve turners\" who on October 11, 2016 simultaneously shut off valves on pipelines carrying Canadian tar sands oil into the U.S. Ward closed the Kinder Morgan / Trans Mountain pipeline near Anacortes, Washington. His first trial ended in a hung jury (Feb 2017); a burglary conviction was reversed on appeal in 2019, and the Washington Supreme Court established a state precedent allowing the climate necessity defense.","state":"Oregon","ideologies":["Climate justice","Civil disobedience"],"era":"Climate movement","in_custody":false,"released":true,"cases":[{"institution_name":"Skagit County Superior Court (Mount Vernon, WA)","institution_state":"Washington","charges":"Sabotage and burglary (shutting a Kinder Morgan / Trans Mountain pipeline valve, Oct 11 2016)","arrest_date":"2016-10-11","sentence":"240 hours community service; no jail, no fine (per CLDC reporting)","convicted":"Burglary conviction at retrial, later reversed on appeal (2019)"}]},
