  {"name":"Ben Joldersma","first_name":"Ben","last_name":"Joldersma","description":"Climate activist who served as a support person for the Minnesota \"valve turners\" during the October 11, 2016 coordinated pipeline shut-down in Clearwater County, Minnesota. Charged as a co-defendant with Annette Klapstein and Emily Johnston, he was acquitted of all charges in October 2018.","ideologies":["Climate justice","Civil disobedience"],"era":"Climate movement","in_custody":false,"released":true,"cases":[{"institution_name":"Clearwater County District Court","institution_state":"Minnesota","charges":"Aiding/abetting criminal damage to critical energy infrastructure (support role, Oct 11 2016)","arrest_date":"2016-10-11","convicted":"No — acquitted October 2018"}]},
  {"name":"Loren Reed","first_name":"Loren","last_name":"Reed","description":"A Dine (Navajo) man and rapper from Page, Arizona, jailed in federal pretrial detention for more than ten months without bail over heated and satirical Facebook posts in a private chat organizing a local police-brutality protest. After an acquaintance reported him and an undercover FBI agent infiltrated the group, he was charged with the federal offense of threatening to damage a building by fire — speech the CLDC argued was First Amendment-protected and never a true threat. (Article predates his 2021 trial; final disposition not stated.)","state":"Arizona","race":"Native American","gender":"Male","ideologies":["Indigenous rights","Free speech","Black Lives Matter solidarity"],"era":"2020 racial justice uprising","in_custody":false,"released":true,"cases":[{"institution_name":"CoreCivic detention center, Florence, Arizona","institution_state":"Arizona","charges":"Threats to damage and destroy a building by means of fire (18 U.S.C.) over Facebook posts about a BLM protest","arrest_date":"2020-06-02","incarceration_date":"2020-06-02"}]},
