  {"name":"Jazmine Jourdan","first_name":"Jazmine","last_name":"Jourdan","description":"Racial-justice activist and Black Unity leader pushed to the ground and beaten by Springfield, Oregon police at the July 29, 2020 Black Unity march, then charged with assault of an officer, interfering, and felony riot. After two years of prosecution, all charges were dismissed mid-trial in June 2022 — the last of the Springfield BLM criminal cases to end — and she joined CLDC's civil-rights suit against the police.","state":"Oregon","race":"Black","gender":"Female","ideologies":["Black Lives Matter","Racial justice","Abolition"],"affiliation":["Black Unity"],"era":"2020 racial justice uprising","in_custody":false,"released":true,"cases":[{"institution_name":"Lane County Circuit Court (Springfield, OR)","institution_state":"Oregon","charges":"Assault of a public safety officer; interfering with a police officer; felony riot (July 29, 2020 Black Unity march)","arrest_date":"2020-07-29","convicted":"No — all charges dismissed mid-trial June 2022"}]},
